.TH man_simple_shell.(1)

.Sh NAME
.B hsh
- user interface to perform some task.

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
The hsh shell is a command-line interpreter. It provides a user interface for Unix-like systems. The shell can be used in both interactive and non-interactive mode.

.B OVERVIEW
The shell, when intialized runs the prompt, then waits for user input. The shell then determines if the user input is a builtin command, sourced from PATH or incompatible.

.B INTERACTIVE MODE
Commands that are run from the keyboard.

.B NON-INTERACTIVE MODE
Commands that are piped into ./hsh from anywhere outside of our shell.

.B BUILTINS
this section lists the builtin commmands that the user may input. "env", "exit", "help".

.SH EXIT STATUS
To exit the program, the user may type "exit" to exit the program.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
PWD contains the current directory.
PATH contains the lsit of directories where executable files are located.

.SH SEE ALSO
.I echo(1), environ(7), systctl(8)

.SH BUGS
No known bugs.

.SH AUTHOR
Simon Sun and Stratton Brooks
